---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Logo from '../components/Logo.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Belvedere Decks | Maryland Composite Deck Builder, Based in Montgomery County"
  description="Maryland's straight-answer deck company. Premium TimberTech and Trex decks with published pricing, an exact price at your kitchen table the same visit, and a 10-year workmanship warranty."
>
  <section class="hero" style="min-height: calc(100vh - 72px); display: flex; flex-direction: column; padding: 0;">
    <div class="container" style="flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; padding-top: 64px; padding-bottom: 64px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Serving Maryland · Based in Montgomery County</p>
      <Logo class="hero-lockup" />
      <h1 style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 3.75rem); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        Your exact deck price,<br />same visit.
      </h1>
      <p class="lead" style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        Most deck companies make you wait a week for a number. We measure your deck,
        build your estimate on the iPad in front of you, and hand you an exact price
        before we leave, with three options and nothing hidden.
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a class="btn primary" href="/estimate" style="padding: 16px 32px;">Get a Free Estimate</a>
        <a class="btn ghost" href="/pricing" style="padding: 16px 32px;">See What Decks Really Cost</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-bar">
      <div class="container">
        <p>TimberTech &amp; Trex Installer · 10-Year Workmanship Warranty · Permits &amp; Inspections Handled · Serving Maryland</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proof-bar">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cells">
        <div>
          <p class="big">Published Pricing</p>
          <p class="label">Real numbers, in writing, before we visit</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="big">Same-Visit Price</p>
          <p class="label">Exact, on the iPad, in your kitchen</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="big">10-Year Warranty</p>
          <p class="label">Workmanship, in writing</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Two ways to get a new deck</p>
      <h2>Only pay for what your deck actually needs.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Most Maryland decks built between 1985 and 2010 sit on a frame with decades of
        life left, under boards and railings that are done. We inspect honestly and
        match the project to the deck, not to our invoice.
      </p>
      <div class="grid cols-3" style="margin-top: 36px;">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Deck Resurfacing</h3>
          <p class="price">$8,000–$35,000</p>
          <p>Your frame stays. New composite boards only, or boards plus new railings for the complete transformation. Two levels, explained in plain English.</p>
          <a href="/services/deck-resurfacing">Compare the two levels →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>New Deck Builds</h3>
          <p class="price">$25,000–$75,000+</p>
          <p>Fully custom: designed, engineered, permitted, and inspected. Includes tearing out an old deck and building new. One design visit, fixed price.</p>
          <a href="/services/new-deck-builds">New build details →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>What Decks Really Cost</h3>
          <p class="price">Real numbers</p>
          <p>We're the only deck company around publishing actual project pricing. Read it before anyone sits in your kitchen, including what cheap bids leave out.</p>
          <a href="/pricing">See the pricing →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Why homeowners choose us</p>
      <h2>The parts of a deck you can't see at the barbecue.</h2>
      <div class="grid cols-2" style="margin-top: 24px;">
        <div>
          <h3>Prices in writing, before we visit</h3>
          <p>Read <a href="/pricing">what decks really cost</a> before anyone sits in your kitchen. No other deck company will put that in writing.</p>
          <h3>Code-first construction</h3>
          <p>Footings dug below the frost line. Waterproof flashing where the deck meets your house. Steel connectors with every fastener hole filled. These are the things cheap bids quietly skip, and exactly what we show you on your own deck.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>10-year workmanship warranty</h3>
          <p>In writing, on every project, on top of the 25–50-year manufacturer warranties on TimberTech and Trex boards.</p>
          <h3>Permits handled, start to finish</h3>
          <p>Building permits, county inspections, and HOA paperwork are our job, not yours. <a href="/montgomery-county-deck-permits">Read our permit guide</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">How it works</p>
      <h2>From first call to finished deck.</h2>
      <table class="stack">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>1. Call or book</th><td>Tell us about the deck by phone, or pick a time on the <a href="/estimate">live calendar</a>. Either way, you get an honest price range up front.</td></tr>
          <tr><th>2. The visit</th><td>We walk the deck together and tell you what we find, good and bad. Then we measure and build your actual price on the iPad while you watch.</td></tr>
          <tr><th>3. Three options</th><td>Good, better, and best options for the parts of the deck you see and touch: the deck boards, railings, and fascia. The same code-perfect structure sits under every tier. We never tier the safety.</td></tr>
          <tr><th>4. The build</th><td>Permits and inspections handled, a clean site every night, and a final walkthrough on your finished deck.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p style="margin-top: 20px;"><a class="btn primary" href="/estimate">Get a Free Estimate</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section dark">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Where we work</p>
      <h2>Anywhere in Maryland we can serve well.</h2>
      <p>
        Most of our work is in Montgomery County:
        <a href="/towns/potomac">Potomac</a>,
        <a href="/towns/north-potomac-kentlands">North Potomac &amp; Kentlands</a>,
        <a href="/towns/bethesda">Bethesda</a>,
        <a href="/towns/olney">Olney</a>,
        <a href="/towns/boyds">Boyds</a>, and
        <a href="/towns/clarksburg">Clarksburg</a>.
        If you're elsewhere in the state, call. If we can get to you, we'll build for you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
